						<h3>Datapoint</h3>
						<p>A datapoint is structured into <code>inferences</code>, <code>input</code>, and <code>metrics</code>.</p>
						<pre>
{
  "_id":[string][unique id],
  "inferences":{
    "1":[float][value in 1 hr],
    "3":[float][value in 3 hrs],
    "6":[float][value in 6 hrs],
    "12":[float][value in 12 hrs],
    "24":[float][value in 24 hrs],
    "48":[float][value in 48 hrs],
    "96":[float][value in 96 hrs]
  },
  "input":{
    "delta":[float][value change from last hour],
    "value":[float][value for current hour],
    "volume":[float][volume for current hour]
  },
  "metrics":{
    "1":[float][MAPE for 1 hr inference],
    "3":[float][MAPE for 3 hr inference],
    "6":[float][MAPE for 6 hr inference],
    "12":[float][MAPE for 12 hr inference],
    "24":[float][MAPE for 24 hr inference],
    "48":[float][MAPE for 48 hr inference],
    "96":[float][MAPE for 96 hr inference]
  },
  "timestamp":[int][current unixtime]
}
						</pre>
						<hr>

						<h3>Examples</h3>
						<p><code>GET /api</code></p>
						<p>This will return a listing of all available markets, as well as some trivial statistics concerning those markets.</p>
						<hr>	

						<p><code>GET /api?market=btceUSD</code></p>
						<p>If the market argument is included, the response will default to ticker, returning the latest datapoint pertaining to that market.
						<hr>

						<p><code>GET /api?market=btceUSD&start=1313334000&end=1470600000</code></p>
						<p>For backtesting old data, a range of time can be specified using the <code>start</code> and <code>end</code> arguments. Either or both can be specified. When specifying a range, the <code>market</code> argument is required. A list of datapoints will be returned.</p>
